<p><b>Spread-spectrum</b> techniques are methods by which <a href="/wiki/Electromagnetic_radiation" title="Electromagnetic radiation">electromagnetic energy</a> generated in a particular <a href="/wiki/Bandwidth_(signal_processing)" title="Bandwidth (signal processing)">bandwidth</a> is deliberately spread in the <a href="/wiki/Frequency_domain" title="Frequency domain">frequency domain</a>, resulting in a <a href="/wiki/Signal_(electrical_engineering)" title="Signal (electrical engineering)" class="mw-redirect">signal</a> with a wider bandwidth. These techniques are used for a variety of reasons, including the establishment of secure communications, increasing resistance to natural <a href="/wiki/Interference" title="Interference">interference</a> and <a href="/wiki/Radio_jamming" title="Radio jamming">jamming</a>, and to prevent detection.</p>
